===Etymology===
{{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} minimally reconstructs {{och-l|劍|tr= {{IPAfont|*kams}}}} and proposes a possible native origin, from ''*k-''nominalized adjective {{och-l|剡|tr= {{IPAfont|*jamʔ}}}}, which is from {{der|zh|sit-pro|*s-rjam||sharp}} and lost its ''*r-'' initial due to folk etymology; doublets {{och-l|磏|tr=*r(i)am|whetstone}} and {{och-l|鐮|sickle}} retain ''*r-''.

Alternatively, the double-edged sword seemingly originated from the {{w|Nanman|southern}} state of {{w|Wu (state)|Wu}} ({{zh-l|*吳}}); so a native Wu term, of unknown linguistic affiliation, might have yielded both {{cog|och|-}} {{och-l|劍}} and {{cog|mkh-vie-pro|*t-kɨəm}} ( > {{cog|vi|gươm}}).

